Additionally, the paper deals with optimization problems that are non-convex, non-differentiable, and non-continuous, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.OH (Other Computer Science). The paper also deals with the concept of monotonicity, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper deals with the iterative application of a map, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.SE (Software Engineering). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SY, cs.RO, cs.DS, cs.OH, and cs.SE, in that order.
